content:
{
  "plan": "Round 1 begins: Initiative order is Scout Kira (17), Bandit_2 (14), Eirik Hearthwise (9), Bandit (3). Kira acts first. She will take a quick shot with her shortbow at Bandit_2: using preroll d20 [6] +4 attack bonus = 10, which misses Bandit_2's AC (12). Kira stays behind cover, preparing for melee if the bandits close in. Next in initiative: Bandit_2. Combat round remains 1 as not all creatures have acted yet.",
  "narration": "Kira flashes a quick, wild grin at your side. With nimble elven grace, she readies her bow, sights down the shaft, and looses an arrow at the nearest bandit—the one ducking low among loose stones. The arrow thunks into a patch of moss just over the bandit's shoulder, missing by inches.\n\nKira mutters, 'Too quick for my liking—stay sharp, Eirik!' She shifts her stance, using a fragment of collapsed wall for scant cover, glancing once to you for resolve.\n\nThe bandits respond to the challenge, teeth bared and weapons raised as the fight heats up atop the windswept overlook.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Bandit_2's turn. Kira’s arrow missed. Bandit_2 (initiative 14) charges toward Kira, scimitar gleaming. Uses prerolled attack: d20 [13] +3 = 16 (hits Kira, her AC is 15). Damage: use first available d6 [5] +1 slashing = 6. Kira drops from 7 to 1 HP. Next: Eirik Hearthwise (player) acts after Bandit_2. Do not prompt the player yet; Bandit_2's action must fully resolve.",
  "narration": "Bandit_2 snarls and breaks from cover, scimitar flashing in the early sun. With a wild yell, he barrels straight for Kira, slashing with brutal intent. The blade catches her just below the ribs—Kira gasps, nearly dropping to one knee as blood darkens her tunic. She grits her teeth, refusing to give the brute the satisfaction of victory, but she’s clearly hurt badly.\n\nThe clash rings across the overlook, steel echoing in the morning mist. Defiance still burns in Kira's eyes, but she fights to stay upright.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Scout Kira",
        "changes": "Takes 6 slashing damage from Bandit_2's scimitar, dropping from 7 to 1 HP."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Eirik Hearthwise uses Healing Word as a bonus action on Kira, restoring 7 HP (1 rolled + 3 Wis + 3 Life Domain). Kira goes from 1 to 8 HP. Eirik now swings with his mace at Bandit_2—player must roll d20+4 for attack. Need the player’s attack roll before proceeding; mace damage (1d6+2) and Bandit_2’s HP changes will be resolved after hit confirmation. Bandit still to act in round 1.",
  "narration": "A bright shimmer of restorative energy leaps from your hand to Kira’s side, closing the ugly gash beneath her ribs. Color comes back to her face and she flashes you a grateful look, a spark of fighting spirit rekindled. You sense the approval of your god—this is what mercy was meant for.\n\nTurning as the healing magic fades, you step forward, raising your mace to strike Bandit_2. The relief in Kira's eyes is matched by the challenge burning in your own.\n\nRoll a d20 and add 4 for your mace attack against Bandit_2 (AC 12). If you hit, you'll then roll 1d6+2 for damage.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Scout Kira",
        "changes": "Healed for 7 hit points by Eirik's Healing Word, rising from 1 to 8 HP."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Eirik Hearthwise",
        "changes": "Expends 1 first-level spell slot for Healing Word (L1 slots now 0/2)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Eirik heals Kira for 7 and then lands a powerful mace strike against Bandit_2. Attack roll 23 easily beats Bandit_2's AC 12; damage roll is 4. Bandit_2 HP drops from 11 to 7. Still to act: Bandit (initiative 3). After Bandit's turn, round 1 will end and combat_round will increment.",
  "narration": "You surge forward as your healing word takes root, swinging your mace with the full weight of both duty and desperation. The bandit who wounded Kira barely raises his guard in time—your blow hammers into his arm, forcing him to stumble back with a howl. He grits his teeth and shakes the pain away, but the thump of your blow leaves no doubt: you are not letting these ruins fall quietly.\n\nKira catches herself on a stone and flashes you a look of deep gratitude. The wind tugs your cloak, the second bandit shuffling on the outskirts, crossbow at the ready and eyes narrowed, seeing the resolve in your team.\n\nThe bandit moves next, weapon gleaming in the rising sun.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 takes 4 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace, HP drops from 11 to 7."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Bandit’s turn (initiative 3). Bandit eyes Eirik—having seen his comrade battered and Kira suddenly restored, he opts to fire his light crossbow at Eirik from medium range. Attack: use Bandit’s first prerolled attack [16] +3 = 19. Eirik’s AC is 16, so this is a hit. Damage: Use next d8 from pool [1] +1 = 2 piercing. Eirik drops from 9 to 7 HP. After this, all creatures have acted in round 1, so increment to combat_round 2 and return to Scout Kira (initiative 17).",
  "narration": "The wary bandit, seeing his companion reeling and Kira suddenly back in the fight, snaps his crossbow up, cheeks pale with adrenaline. He squeezes the trigger—a bolt whistles through the crisp air, slamming into the gap between your scale mail plates and biting deep into your side. A sharp sting and a rush of cold pain flood your senses, but you grit your teeth and keep your shield high.\n\nThe bandit snarls, hastily beginning to reload, just as Kira—now with fresh fire in her eyes—prepares to strike again, the morning mist swirling around her as round two begins.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Eirik Hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 2 piercing damage from a bandit's crossbow bolt, HP drops from 9 to 7."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 begins with Scout Kira's turn. She draws her shortsword and lunges at Bandit_2. Using her first available prerolled attack (d20 [17] +4 = 21), Kira easily strikes Bandit_2 (AC 12). Damage uses d6 [6] +3 = 9. Bandit_2 HP drops from 7 to -2; this drops the bandit and triggers status change to 'dead'. Next to act: Eirik Hearthwise after Bandit_2's turn (but Bandit_2 is now dead, so will be skipped this round). Bandit (initiative 3) remains at 11 HP; will act after Eirik.",
  "narration": "Kira darts forward—a streak of elven speed and wounded pride. Her shortsword flashes silver in the mist, plunging deep into Bandit_2’s side. The brute barely gasps as the steel finds its mark, then crumples to the ground, blade rattling from numbed fingers. Kira pulls her sword free, chest heaving as adrenaline gives way to relief.\n\nShe flashes you a look of fierce gratitude—alive, and still dangerous. With one bandit slain, the second lingers on the tower’s edge, eyes wide with fear, crossbow trembling.\n\nA heartbeat of silence hangs between the battered stones as you step up, shield gleaming and resolve unbroken. The tides have turned—now it’s your move, Eirik.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 takes 9 piercing damage from Kira's shortsword, dropping from 7 HP to -2 HP and dying."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, Eirik's turn. Bandit_2 is dead. Eirik casts Sacred Flame at the remaining bandit (Bandit). Sacred Flame requires the Bandit to make a Dexterity saving throw (DC 13). Use Bandit's available DEX save preroll: 11. Modifier for bandit DEX is +1, so total save = 12. 12 < 13, so the bandit fails the save and takes full damage. Sacred Flame deals 1d8 radiant damage. Use next generic d8 preroll [8]. 8 radiant damage dealt. Bandit HP drops from 11 to 3. After Eirik, Bandit acts to finish round 2.",
  "narration": "As the dust settles from Kira’s decisive strike, you thrust your holy symbol toward the bandit still standing at the tower’s edge. Light blossoms from the stormy sky—a column of searing radiance engulfs him with sudden, blinding force. The bandit shrieks as the divine energy burns across his shoulder and side, leaving angry red streaks and the stink of singed leather. He staggers but remains standing, now clearly desperate and scorched under the judgement of your faith.\n\nHis crossbow clatters to the stones as he fumbles for his scimitar, horror stealing the bravado from his face. The fight isn’t over, but the shadows around you have recoiled from your god’s fury.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit fails Dexterity save (12 vs DC 13) and takes 8 radiant damage from Eirik's Sacred Flame, dropping from 11 HP to 3 HP."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, Bandit's turn. All others have acted: Kira dropped Bandit_2 (dead), Eirik hit Bandit with Sacred Flame (HP 3/11). Bandit, now scorched and desperate, is the last combatant for this round and will choose an attack. Will use available prerolled attack: [2] for scimitar (since he lost his crossbow), which is a miss. After the Bandit's action, all living combatants will have finished their turns—advance to combat_round 3 and return to the top of initiative with Kira.",
  "narration": "The surviving bandit, still ablaze with residual divine radiance, tosses his crossbow aside and rushes at you with a scream, slashing his scimitar in wide, panicked arcs. But the blade glances harmlessly off your shield, his fear robbing him of precision. The clash of metal rings through the mist, but your resolve holds unbroken.\n\nEirik stands firm as his foe falters, and Kira—eyes bright and sword red—flanks the bandit for the next blow. Another round is about to begin, the sun breaking through the clouds as the tide of battle shifts for good.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Scout Kira's turn. The initiative order is: Kira (alive), Bandit_2 (dead), Eirik (alive), Bandit (alive). Kira will use her shortsword on the remaining bandit, who is at 3 HP. She uses her first available prerolled attack: d20 [1] +4 = 5, which misses. No damage. The bandit is still standing. Next up is Eirik Hearthwise's turn. Do not prompt the player yet; describe Kira's action first.",
  "narration": "Kira leaps at the desperate bandit, her shortsword slicing through the mist. But his fear sharpens his reflexes—he ducks low, and her blade whistles harmlessly above his head. She hisses with frustration, circling to keep him boxed in.\n\nThe last foe is battered, wild-eyed, and cornered between you both, but he’s not out just yet. The air is tense with the charge of battle; Kira breaths hard, flicking her eyes to you—now is the time to strike.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's turn. Kira just missed with her shortsword and the bandit remains at 3 HP. Eirik is now up in initiative. Await the player's attack roll (mace: d20+4 vs AC 12). If hit, the player will then roll for damage (1d6+2). Bandit will act after Eirik. Combat_round remains 3 until all creatures act.",
  "narration": "Kira’s blade glances off stone, but you charge straight in while the bandit darts away from her reach. The battered foe looks between you, sweat streaming down his temples—he knows there’s no escape. \n\nSteel and prayer steady your hand as you heft your mace and swing in a broad arc, aiming to end this once and for all.\n\nRoll a d20 and add 4 for your mace attack against the bandit (his AC is 12). If you strike true, follow up with 1d6+2 for damage.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Eirik's mace attack roll 21 easily hits the bandit's AC 12. Awaiting the player's damage roll (1d6+2). Bandit is at 3 HP—if the damage is 3 or higher, the bandit will be defeated. After Eirik's attack resolves, the bandit gets his turn to close round 3.",
  "narration": "You step into the arc of Kira’s missed slash and bring your mace down with righteous force. The bandit’s desperate parry comes too late—your weapon descends like a judge’s gavel, the blow destined to end his resistance.\n\nNow, roll 1d6 and add 2 to see how much power you deliver with your strike.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's attack resolves. His mace lands a blow for 4 damage against the bandit, who had 3 HP. This drops the bandit from 3 to -1 HP, killing him. All hostiles are now dead. Initiative has cycled this round; combat_round will increment to 4 for recordkeeping, and the encounter will immediately end with 'exit' action.",
  "narration": "Your mace smashes into the side of the bandit's head with a solid, bone-shaking thud. He stumbles, eyes wide in pain and shock, then collapses to the shattered stones beneath your boots. The final echo of battle fades from the overlook—the only sound now Kira's ragged breaths and the distant song of morning birds returning to the dawn-split sky.\n\nKira stands slowly, blade slack at her side, a tired and relieved smile playing on her lips. The North Tower Overlook is yours. No enemy remains to threaten it, at least for today.",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit takes 4 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace, dropping from 3 HP to -1 HP and dying. Status: dead."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Combat Summary: {
  "narration": "At dawn atop the North Tower Overlook, Eirik Hearthwise and Scout Kira faced off against two hardened bandits intent on reclaiming the ruins. The battle was fierce and swift. Kira’s initial arrow missed, and the bandits pressed their attack, severely wounding Kira. Eirik responded quickly with Healing Word, restoring her vitality, then struck back with his mace, wounding the aggressor. The bandits retaliated, landing a crossbow bolt into Eirik's side, but the duo held fast. Kira rallied, landing a decisive shortsword strike that felled one bandit. Eirik then cast Sacred Flame, scorching the last foe who desperately closed in. As the bandit attempted to flee Kira’s blades, Eirik’s final mace blow brought him crashing down, concluding the fight. Two bandit corpses lay scattered on the battered stones while the dawn chorus returned. The party earned a total of 50 experience points for vanquishing their foes, divided equally between Eirik and Kira (25 XP each). The North Tower Overlook was secured—for now.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Eirik Hearthwise",
        "changes": "HP 7/11, Status alive, Condition none, Spell Slots L1:0/2"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Scout Kira",
        "changes": "HP 8/10, Status alive, Condition none"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "North Tower Overlook Bandit Skirmish",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 defeated with HP -2/11, status dead; Bandit defeated with HP 0/11, status dead"
      }
    }
  ]
}
